## Why This Is Asked
Tests practical understanding of ephemeral cross‑account access, least privilege, VPC endpoints, and auditability. It also probes revocation semantics for temporary credentials.

## Key Concepts
- STS AssumeRole with session duration
- Cross‑account IAM roles and trust policies
- S3 bucket policies with resource and condition constraints
- VPC Endpoint restrictions
- CloudTrail auditing
- Revocation mechanics for temporary credentials

## Code Example
```javascript
// trust policy example (role in data owner account)
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": {"AWS": "arn:aws:iam::PARTNER_AWS_ACCOUNT:role/PartnerDataAccess"},
      "Action": "sts:AssumeRole",
      "Condition": {"StringEquals": {"sts:ExternalId": "data-exchange-2026"}}
    }
  ]
}
```

```json
// bucket policy snippet (only for the assumed role and specific VPC endpoint)
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": {"AWS": "arn:aws:iam::PARTNER_AWS_ACCOUNT:role/PartnerDataAccess"},
      "Action": ["s3:GetObject","s3:ListBucket"],
      "Resource": [
        "arn:aws:s3:::partner-data-bucket",
        "arn:aws:s3:::partner-data-bucket/*"
      ],
      "Condition": {"StringEquals": {"aws:SourceVpce": "vpce-EXAMPLE"}}
    }
  ]
}
```

