## Why This Is Asked
Tests understanding of cross‑account access, least privilege, and data isolation in S3 with AWS IAM roles and bucket policies. It also touches on revocation and testing in a real-world partner scenario.

## Key Concepts
- Cross‑account IAM trust and role policies
- S3 bucket policies and per‑prefix access
- Least privilege and access revocation
- Private access options (VPC endpoint) and public access controls

## Code Example
```javascript
// Trust policy (role in data account)
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": {"AWS": "arn:aws:iam::<PartnerAcct>:root"},
      "Action": "sts:AssumeRole"
    }
  ]
}
```

```javascript
// Role policy: s3:GetObject on partner prefix
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": "s3:GetObject",
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::data-bucket/partner-prefix/*"
    }
  ]
}
```

```javascript
// Bucket policy: allow role to read
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": {"AWS": "arn:aws:iam::<DataAcct>:role/PartnerReadRole"},
      "Action": "s3:GetObject",
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::data-bucket/partner-prefix/*"
    }
  ]
}
```

